In the [[United States]], a '''loosie''' (or '''loosey''') is a single [[cigarette]] that is purchased or sold.

The transaction is illegal and commonly found in low-income areas.<ref name="huff_ILov">{{Cite web| title = I Love 'Loosies': In Defense of Black Market Cigarettes| author = Christopher Mathias| work = The Huffington Post| date = 2011-04-06| accessdate = 2015-11-16| url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/christopher-mathias/i-love-loosies-in-defense_b_845698.html}}</ref> The high cost of cigarettes due to increased taxation has been blamed for increased sales of loosies.<ref name="nyti_OnMa">{{Cite web| title = On Manhattan Streets, Loosie Men Sell Illegal Smokes| last = Goldstein | first = Joseph| work = nytimes.com| date = 4 April 2011| accessdate = 2017-10-30| url = https://www.nytimes.com/2011/04/05/nyregion/05loosie.html| quote = 
}}</ref><ref name="oakl_Prop">{{Cite web| title = Proposed $2 cigarette tax sparks fear of sale of “loosies”| author = | work = Oakland North| date = | accessdate = 2017-10-30| url = https://oaklandnorth.net/2016/10/19/proposed-2-cigarette-tax-sparks-fear-of-loosies/| quote = loosies}}</ref> 

In 2014, [[Eric Garner]] died when NYPD officers attempted to arrest him for allegedly selling loosies.<ref name="vice_HowI">{{Cite web| title = How Illegal Cigarettes Get Smuggled and Sold in New York City| author = Solange Uwimana| work = Vice| date = 2014-10-23| accessdate = 2015-11-16| url = https://www.vice.com/read/i-spent-a-day-with-a-guy-selling-illegal-cigarettes-on-the-streets-of-nyc-1023}}</ref>

