{{more footnotes|date=May 2013}} '''National Biomedical Imaging Archive''' (NBIA) is an [[Open-source software]] [[Web application]] managed by the [[United States]] [[National Cancer Institute|National Cancer Institute (NCI)]] intended to create searchable repositories of [[in vivo]] images.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/NBIA/National+Biomedical+Imaging+Archive+-+NBIA|title = National Biomedical Imaging Archive - NBIA - Imaging - NBIA - National Cancer Institute - Confluence Wiki|website = wiki.nci.nih.gov|access-date = 2016-03-29}}</ref> The software is described in detail and can be downloaded from the [https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/NBIA/National+Biomedical+Imaging+Archive+-+NBIA NBIA wiki]. A [https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/NBIA/NBIA+Refactoring+Analysis+Project re-factoring analysis] which examined the current status of development and future strategies was completed in 2015 and published on the NCI wiki. A demo instance of NBIA is deployed at http://imaging.nci.nih.gov/. Initially this was leveraged by NCI's [http://imaging.cancer.gov/ Cancer Imaging Program] to support the data sharing needs of the cancer imaging research community, but most of that data has been migrated to [[The Cancer Imaging Archive (TCIA)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://wiki.nci.nih.gov/display/CIP/NBIA+at+CBIIT+Image+Collections|title = NBIA at CBIIT Image Collections - Imaging - Cancer Imaging Program - National Cancer Institute - Confluence Wiki|website = wiki.nci.nih.gov|access-date = 2016-03-29}}</ref> TCIA continues to leverage the NBIA software as part of its infrastructure.<ref>{{Cite journal|last = Clark|first = Kenneth|last2 = Vendt|first2 = Bruce|last3 = Smith|first3 = Kirk|last4 = Freymann|first4 = John|last5 = Kirby|first5 = Justin|last6 = Koppel|first6 = Paul|last7 = Moore|first7 = Stephen|last8 = Phillips|first8 = Stanley|last9 = Maffitt|first9 = David|date = 2013-07-25|title = The Cancer Imaging Archive (TCIA): Maintaining and Operating a Public Information Repository|url = https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10278-013-9622-7|journal = Journal of Digital Imaging|language = en|volume = 26|issue = 6|pages = 1045–1057|doi = 10.1007/s10278-013-9622-7|issn = 0897-1889|pmc = 3824915|pmid = 23884657}}</ref>
