{{Orphan|date=June 2018}}

The '''Order of Pharmacists of Lebanon''' is a pharmaceutical organisation based in [[Beirut]].

It formed a partnership with the [[Royal Pharmaceutical Society]] in February 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=RPS agrees partnership with Lebanese pharmacy association|url=https://www.pharmaceutical-journal.com/20204410.article?|accessdate=2 April 2018|publisher=Pharmaceutical Journal|date=16 February 2018}}</ref>

More than 1,800 pharmacists attended its 24th Annual Congress in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pharmacy in the Arab countries look towards the UK as gold standard|url=https://www.pharmaceutical-journal.com/opinion/blogs/pharmacy-in-the-arab-countries-look-towards-the-uk-as-gold-standard/20202108.blog|accessdate=2 April 2018|publisher=Pharmaceutical Journal|date=19 December 2016}}</ref>

It is supported by [[Michel Aoun]] the President of Lebanon.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Order of Pharmacists of Lebanon inaugurates its 25th annual congress "The Seven-Star Pharmacist: Shaping the Future of Pharmacy in Lebanon"|url=http://web-release.info/order-pharmacists-lebanon-inaugurates-25th-annual-congress-seven-star-pharmacist-shaping-future-pharmacy-lebanon/|accessdate=2 April 2018|publisher=Web Release|date=19 November 2017}}</ref>

